        <p>And the no-cost options, which work just as well if you're disciplined:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>YNAB (You Need a Budget)</strong> — the best <em>system</em> for people living paycheck to paycheck. Paid, with a free trial; worth it if the method clicks for you. (We don't earn anything on YNAB — it's here because it's good.)</li>
          <li><strong>A simple spreadsheet</strong> — if apps feel like overhead, a Google Sheet with income minus fixed costs minus savings target gives you your weekly spending number in five minutes. Free.</li>
          <li><strong>Your bank's own app</strong> — most now have spending categorization built in. Less friction than a separate tool, and free.</li>
        </ul>

